                            <comment id="17793749" author="emilles" created="Wed, 6 Dec 2023 14:33:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You can add a type argument until this gets fixed:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-groovy&quot;&gt;
Try.of{ option() }.&amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Integer&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;mapTry(Option::get)
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//                 ^^^^^^^^^&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17793750" author="chrylis" created="Wed, 6 Dec 2023 14:41:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Type witnesses do seem to work around the problem, but this would mean&lt;br/&gt;
retrofitting the whole codebase, so for now in practicals terms we&apos;ll have&lt;br/&gt;
to stick with 4.0.14.&lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
                            <comment id="17793763" author="emilles" created="Wed, 6 Dec 2023 14:53:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There is also an open ticket for adding support for method reference type args: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-9239&quot; title=&quot;Java compatibility: consider supporting method reference with generics&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-9239&quot;&gt;GROOVY-9239&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17793768" author="emilles" created="Wed, 6 Dec 2023 15:04:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d have to pull down 4.0.14 to see why this passed STC previously.  Looking at the current implementation, it appears you may have slipped through a crack before.  The type of the &lt;tt&gt;Option::get&lt;/tt&gt; expression by itself is &lt;tt&gt;Closure&amp;lt;T&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt; or &lt;tt&gt;Closure&amp;lt;Object&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt;.  Only by incorporating the context of &lt;tt&gt;Option&amp;lt;Integer&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt; can we work out &lt;tt&gt;Closure&amp;lt;Integer&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt; or &lt;tt&gt;CheckedFunction1&amp;lt;Option&amp;lt;Integer&amp;gt;,Integer&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt;.  I don&apos;t think 4.0.14 does this and certainly 4.0.16 doesn&apos;t.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17793834" author="emilles" created="Wed, 6 Dec 2023 16:36:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/groovy/commit/5ec0d02ac19b44cc62bf02a4804cb0130276bdd9&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/groovy/commit/5ec0d02ac19b44cc62bf02a4804cb0130276bdd9&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17793911" author="emilles" created="Wed, 6 Dec 2023 19:42:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t have a solution yet for Groovy 4.  It is mixing &quot;T&quot; from &lt;tt&gt;Option&lt;/tt&gt; and &quot;T&quot; from &lt;tt&gt;Try&lt;/tt&gt;.  In 4.0.14 this worked in your favor, resulting in &quot;T=Integer&quot;.  4.0.16 gets &quot;T=Option&amp;lt;Integer&amp;gt;&quot; at the point of &lt;tt&gt;mapTry(Option::get)&lt;/tt&gt; which is incorrect.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If I try and stop the mixing at the same point where the Groovy 5 fix went in, it cannot work out &quot;T=Integer&quot; and ends up with &quot;T=Object&quot; which is the erasure of &quot;T&quot; from &lt;tt&gt;Option&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Update: it is fixed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17794289" author="emilles" created="Thu, 7 Dec 2023 15:13:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/groovy/commit/c5cee21bd66909fc8ca800198c001d63849d8a77&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/groovy/commit/c5cee21bd66909fc8ca800198c001d63849d8a77&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
